# ─── Capacitor / Android build artifacts ───
# We commit the android/ source (Gradle config, AndroidManifest,
# Java/Kotlin source) for reproducible builds. We ignore everything
# Gradle/Android Studio regenerates on each build.
android/.gradle/
android/.idea/
android/build/
android/app/build/
android/app/release/
android/captures/
android/local.properties
android/keystore/
android/*.iml
android/app/*.iml
android/app/google-services.json
.capacitor/
*.keystore
*.jks

# ─── Avatar processing temp dir ───
# Used by scripts/process-male-avatars-step1-bgremove.mjs to drop
# transparent PNGs before sharp re-encodes them to WebP. Large files,
# regenerated on every avatar refresh — never commit.
.tmp-bg-removed/

# ─── Unity-as-Library build artifacts ───
# When Phase 1 of the Unity 3D avatar lands (see docs/unity-as-library.md),
# Unity Editor's "Export Project" drops a unityLibrary/ Gradle module
# into android/. We commit the SOURCE of that module (build.gradle, the
# Java/Kotlin/.so files Unity generated, AndroidManifest) but ignore
# everything Gradle regenerates when AGP rebuilds the .aar.
# Without these excludes, a single build commits +200 MB of Gradle cache.
android/unityLibrary/build/
android/unityLibrary/.gradle/
android/unityLibrary/local.properties
android/unityLibrary/*.iml
android/unityLibrary/.idea/

# ─── Capacitor / iOS build artifacts ───
# Same logic as Android: commit the ios/ source (Info.plist, Swift
# source, Podfile) but ignore everything Xcode/CocoaPods regenerates.
# The ios/ folder is created by `npx cap add ios` on macOS — see
# docs/capacitor-ios-setup.md for the Codemagic cloud-build path.
ios/App/Pods/
ios/App/build/
ios/DerivedData/
ios/App/Podfile.lock
ios/.sourcery/
ios/App/output/
ios/App/App/public/
*.xcuserstate
*.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/
*.mobileprovision
*.p12
*.p8
